{
  "local_port": 35080,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply for commercial gas connection in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Applying for a commercial gas connection in Bangalore involves several steps. Here's a comprehensive guide to help you through the process:\n\n### 1. **Identify the Gas Provider**\nIn Bangalore, commercial gas connections are typically provided by **Indane (Indian Oil)**, **Bharat Gas**, or **HP Gas**. You can choose the provider based on your preference and availability in your area.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Eligibility**\nYou must have a valid commercial space (restaurant, hotel, bakery, etc.) with a registered business to apply for a commercial gas connection.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Documents Required**\nPrepare the following documents:\n   - Proof of Identity (Aadhaar Card, PAN Card, Passport, etc.).\n   - Proof of Address (Electricity Bill, Property Tax Receipt, Rent Agreement, etc.).\n   - Business registration certificate (GST Certificate, Shop Act License, etc.).\n   - Passport-sized photographs.\n   - No Objection Certificate (NOC) from the building owner (if applicable).\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Application Process**\n   - **Online Application**: Visit the official website of the gas provider (e.g., [Indane](https://www.indane.co.in/), [Bharat Gas](https://www.bharatgas.com/), or [HP Gas](https://www.hindustanpetroleum.com/hp-gas)) and fill out the application form for a commercial gas connection.\n   - **Offline Application**: Visit the nearest LPG distributor of the chosen gas provider and collect the application form. Submit the filled form along with the required documents.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Payment**\nPay the necessary fees, which include:\n   - Security deposit for the gas cylinder.\n   - Refill charges.\n   - Installation charges (if applicable).\n\nPayment can be made online (via the gas provider's website) or offline (cash/cheque) at the distributor's office.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Verification**\nAfter submitting the application, the gas provider will verify your documents and conduct an inspection of the commercial premises to ensure safety compliance.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Installation**\nOnce the verification is complete, the gas provider will schedule the installation of the gas connection, including the regulator and cylinder.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Safety Guidelines**\nEnsure that your commercial space complies with the safety guidelines for LPG usage, including proper ventilation and fire safety measures.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Refill Booking**\nAfter the connection is active, you can book refills online or by contacting the distributor directly. Most providers offer online refill booking through their websites or mobile apps.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Customer Support**\nFor any queries or assistance, contact the customer care helpline of your gas provider or visit the distributor's office.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, you can successfully apply for a commercial gas connection in Bangalore.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
